description: Internazionale and Feyenoord have met on three previous occasions in Europe, with both sides winning one game each. Those two victories have both been achieved by the away side, with Feyenoord winning in Italy in April 2002 and Internazionale winning in the Netherlands last week. Feyenoord are winless in their last eight away matches against Italian sides in European competition, and haven’t managed to win any of their 12 overall matches there by more than a single goal.

title: Lazio vs Viktoria Plzeň - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 2nd Leg
description: Lazio have only hosted a Czechia side once in a knockout match in major European competition, losing 3-0 against Sparta Prague in the UEFA Europa League in March 2016. Viktoria Plzen have lost five of their six away European matches in Italy – including the last four in a row – with their one win coming in a 3-0 success at Napoli in February 2013 in the UEFA Europa League.

title: Bayer Leverkusen vs Bayern Munchen - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 2nd Leg
description: Following their 3-0 victory in the first leg, Bayern Munich could register multiple wins over Bayer Leverkusen in the same campaign for the first time since 2020-21. Bayer Leverkusen are unbeaten in their three home games against Bayern Munich under Xabi Alonso, winning two of them. Prior to Alonso’s arrival, they only won one of their previous eight home matches against Bayern, between 2015-16 and 2021-22.

title: Liverpool vs PSG - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 2nd Leg
description: After losing their first European meeting with Paris SG in April 1997, Liverpool have only lost one of four against them since, winning three of them. None of the last 15 French sides to play away from home against an English opponent in Europe have managed to win, with 14 of those ending in defeats. Indeed, the last such victory was by Paris SG in December 2020 against Manchester United.

title: Manchester United vs Real Sociedad - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 2nd Leg
description: There have only been nine goals scored in seven European meetings between Man Utd and Real Sociedad, with four of those coming in the same game by the Red Devils in a 4-0 win in February 2021. Three of Real Sociedad’s four away European games in England have come at Old Trafford against Man Utd, with their other a 6-0 loss at Liverpool in November 1975.

title: Olympique Lyonnais vs FCSB - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 2nd Leg
description: Lyon are unbeaten in all five of their major European matches against FCSB. They have only faced Sparta Prague more often without losing. FCSB have never won a major away European match in France in six attempts, with this their first visit since losing 2-0 to Lyon in November 2008 in the UEFA Champions League.

title: Lille vs Borussia Dortmund - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 2nd Leg
description: Lille have only won one of their 10 major European meetings with German clubs, beating VfL Wolfsburg 3-1 in December 2021 in the UEFA Champions League. All three of their games with Borussia Dortmund have ended as draws. When Borussia Dortmund have drawn the first leg of a major European knockout tie at home, they have been eliminated in six out of seven instances; the other was against Alania Vladikavkaz in the first round of the 1993-94 UEFA Cup.

title: Arsenal vs PSV - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 2nd Leg
description: Arsenal’s 7-1 victory in the first leg against PSV was the biggest ever away win in the knockout stages of the UEFA Champions League. The only English team to score 10 goals across two legs in the competition was Man City vs Schalke 04 in 2018-19’s last 16. PSV are winless in their last six away major European games in England, with their last two visits defeats to Arsenal. They’ve won four of 20 away games, beating Leeds twice, Newcastle and Spurs.

title: Rangers vs Fenerbahçe - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - R16 - 2nd Leg
description: Rangers are unbeaten in their five home matches against Turkish sides in European competition, conceding only one goal in those five games in a 2-1 win over Galatasaray in October 2020. Rangers have lost just two of their last 14 home games in the UEFA Europa League, though did lose their last game in the knockout stages in March 2024 against Benfica 1-0.

title: Bodo / Glimt vs Lazio - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quarter Finals 1st Leg
description: This will be the first ever European meeting between Bodø/Glimt and Lazio. The Norwegian side have won their last three home European matches against Italian sides, beating Sampdoria in 1994 in the Cup Winners’ Cup and Roma twice in the 2021-22 Conference League. Lazio’s only two previous European meetings with a Norwegian side was in the 2015-16 UEFA Europa League, beating Rosenborg at home and away.

title: Olympique Lyonnais vs Manchester United - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quarter Finals 1st Leg
description: Lyon have never beaten Manchester United in four attempts in major European competitions only facing Barcelona more often without winning in Europe. Manchester United’s two away visits to Lyon have both been in the UEFA Champions League and on both occasions they came from behind to draw, from 2-0 down to draw 2-2 in September 2004 and 1-0 down to draw 1-1 in February 2008.

title: Arsenal vs Real Madrid - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Quarter Finals - 1st Leg
description: This will be just the third meeting between Arsenal and Real Madrid in European competition, following their last 16 tie in the UEFA Champions League in 2005-06. Arsenal won 1-0 in the first leg away from home, before drawing 0-0 at Highbury in the second leg. Since the start of the 2017-18 campaign, Real Madrid have played 22 matches against English sides in the knockout stages of the UEFA Champions League. This is 10 more than any other team against sides from a specific nation in this period, after Liverpool and Manchester City’s 12 meetings each with Spanish teams.

title: Bayern Munchen vs Internazionale - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Quarter Finals - 1st Leg
description: This will be the 10th meeting between Bayern Munich and Internazionale in European competition, with the German side winning five of the previous nine, including the last time they faced each other in the UEFA Champions League. Internazionale have lost four of their seven games against Bayern Munich in the UEFA Champions League, but have eliminated them in both of their meetings in the knockout stages of the competition: 2-0 in the 2009-10 final and progressing on away goals over two legs in 2010-11 in the last 16.

title: Rangers vs Athletic Club - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quarter Finals 1st Leg
description: Rangers and Athletic Club faced in the 1968-69 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup in the quarter-final – the Gers won 4-1 in the first leg at home, before Athletic won 2-0 in the second leg, with the Scottish side going through 4-3 on aggregate. Athletic Club have lost both of their major European visits to Scotland, losing 1-0 to Dunfermline Athletic in 1965 and 4-1 to Rangers in 1969, both in the Inter-Cities Fairs Cup.

title: Tottenham Hotspur vs Eintracht Frankfurt - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quarter Finals 1st Leg
description: Tottenham Hotspur and Eintracht Frankfurt last faced in the UEFA Champions League group stages in 2022-23, with Spurs drawing 0-0 in Germany and winning 3-2 at the Tottenham Hotspur Stadium that season. The only previous European knockout meeting between Spurs and Eintracht Frankfurt was in the 1981-82 Cup Winners’ Cup quarter-final – Spurs won 2-0 at home before losing 2-1 away in the second leg, but progressed 3-2 on aggregate.

title: PSG vs Aston Villa - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Quarter Finals - 1st Leg
description: Paris SG and Aston Villa will meet for the first time in European competition, with this just the second UEFA Champions League quarter-final between French and English sides in the last eight campaigns. Paris SG eliminated Liverpool in the last 16 of this season’s UEFA Champions League, after having exited the competition in each of their last three knockout stage meetings with English sides.

title: Barcelona vs Borussia Dortmund - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Quarter Finals - 1st Leg
description: Barcelona are unbeaten in their five meetings with Borussia Dortmund in European competition, including a victory over them earlier in this season’s UEFA Champions League. Only against Lyon, Napoli and Werder Bremen have they played more in Europe without losing. While Borussia Dortmund haven’t won any of their five games against Barcelona, they’ve only gone six consecutive European matches without beating an opponent against two other sides; one of which is another Spanish team.

title: Manchester United vs Olympique Lyonnais - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quater Finals 2nd Leg
description: This will be the third time that Manchester United have faced Lyon in European competition at Old Trafford, with the Red Devils winning both prior meetings. Lyon have lost just one of their last nine European games against sides from England, a 3-0 defeat to West Ham during the 2021-22 UEFA Europa League.

title: Athletic Club vs Rangers - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quater Finals 2nd Leg
description: Athletic Club have only hosted Rangers once before, beating them 2-0 in the Fairs Cup in April 1969. The only other time Athletic have hosted a Scottish club was in two games against Dunfermline in 1965, also in the Fairs Cup, winning 1-0 and then 2-1 in a deciding game. Rangers won 3-2 away at Real Betis in their last European game in Spain, having gone 13 away games without winning there beforehand between 1962 and 2018.

title: Real Madrid vs Arsenal - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Quarter Finals - 2nd Leg
description: Arsenal remain unbeaten against Real Madrid in European competition, and haven’t conceded a single goal across their three meetings. The Gunners could become the first side ever to keep four consecutive clean sheets against Los Blancos in the European Cup/UEFA Champions League. Real Madrid’s defeat at the Emirates Stadium was the fifth time they have lost the first leg of a knockout stage tie in the European Cup/UEFA Champions League by 3+ goals, while they’ve been eliminated in the second leg in three of the previous four occasions.

title: Internazionale vs Bayern Munchen - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Quarter Finals - 2nd Leg
description: The last six meetings between Internazionale and Bayern Munich in the UEFA Champions League have seen both sides win three times each, while only one of those six victories has been achieved by the team playing at home. Bayern Munich have won all four of their away games against Internazionale in European competition, including all three in the UEFA Champions League without conceding a single goal. Indeed, this is the Italian side’s longest losing streak at home to an opponent across all European competitions.

title: Eintracht Frankfurt vs Tottenham Hotspur - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quater Finals 2nd Leg
description: Eintracht Frankfurt have only won one of their five meetings with Tottenham in European competition. However, that lone victory came on the only occasion in which they’ve hosted them in a knockout stage match, beating them 2-1 in the Cup Winners’ Cup quarter-final in 1981-82. Tottenham have lost six of their last seven knockout stage games away to German opponents in Europe, while failing to score in four of their last five such matches. They lost 3-0 in the most recent of these, being eliminated by RB Leipzig in the last 16 of the UEFA Champions League in 2019-20.

title: Lazio Bodø / vs Glimt - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quater Finals 2nd Leg
description: Lazio’s only previous meeting with Bodø/Glimt was in the 2-0 defeat in the first leg of this tie. They last hosted a Norwegian side back in October 2015, beating Rosenborg 3-1 in the UEFA Europa League. Bodø/Glimt are winless in all six of their European trips to Italy, drawing one and losing five. Their last away game in Italy was in a quarter-final second leg, losing 4-0 to Roma in the 2021-22 Conference League.

title: Athletic Club vs Manchester United - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Semi Finals 1st Leg
description: This is the first European meeting between Athletic Club and Manchester United since the 2011-12 UEFA Europa League last 16 – under Marcelo Bielsa, Athletic won both legs and eventually reached that season’s final. Manchester United have lost three out of four European matches against Athletic Club, with their one win coming back in February 1957 in the second leg of that season’s European Cup quarter-final, a 3-0 victory at Old Trafford which took them into the semi-final 6-5 on aggregate.

title: Tottenham Hotspur vs Bodø / Glimt - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Semi Finals 1st Leg
description: Tottenham Hotspur and Bodø/Glimt have never previously faced each other in any competition. Spurs have won all four of their previous European games against Norwegian teams, beating Lyn 6-3 and 6-0 in the 1972-73 UEFA Cup and Tromsø 3-0 and 2-0 in the 2013-14 UEFA Europa League. Bodø/Glimt have lost all three of their European meetings with English clubs, losing home and away against Arsenal in the 2022-23 UEFA Europa League, while they lost 3-2 away at Man Utd earlier this campaign in the group stages.

title: Arsenal vs PSG - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Semi Finals - 1st Leg
description: This will be the sixth meeting between Arsenal and Paris SG, while the Gunners are unbeaten across the previous five. Arsenal are the opponent that the French side have faced the most times in European competition without ever winning. Arsenal have already beaten Paris SG in the UEFA Champions League this season, winning 2-0 at the Emirates Stadium in the league phase last October. Only one English side have beaten Paris SG twice in a single edition of the competition: Manchester City in the 2020-21 semi-finals.

description: Barcelona and Internazionale have faced each other on 16 previous occasions in Europe, with the Spanish side winning exactly half of those.
